about.summary: A tool for retrieving Streamflow from the GEOGloWS ECMWF Streamflow service developed by Riley Hales as part of a Master's Thesis in Civil and Environmental Engineering at Brigham Young University

name: geoglows
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "geoglows" %}
{% set version = "0.14.3" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 58e6460cc0b3eef1224967fc01c8f38834f9aa5328b40bac308ec719d3ac2b4d

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - requests
    - plotly
    - jinja2
    - pandas
    - shapely
    - scipy

test:
  imports:
    - geoglows

about:
  home: https://github.com/rileyhales/geoglows
  summary: A tool for retrieving Streamflow from the GEOGloWS ECMWF Streamflow service developed by Riley Hales as part of a Master's Thesis in Civil and Environmental Engineering at Brigham Young University
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE
  doc_url: https://geoglows.readthedocs.io

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - rileyhales
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.7.0
